6:
We're doing it, you guys. We're doing
a Fortunebringer race for Palpebra
this year!
10: Alk, Ellya's making up words again.
15:
Rude! But it's fine. I can use this
opportunity to educate you on
some Yamato culture.
20:
You're really into Yamato culture
lately, huh?
23:
So, what's this "Fortunebringer race"
supposed to be?
26:
It's basically a footrace held
throughout a city. Whoever wins
earns the title of that year's
Fortunebringer!
31:
Hmph. A real man makes his own
fortune.
35:
Oh? Sounds to me like you're too
chicken to enter. Hehe.
39:
But anyway, the important thing is
that ANYONE can enter! And that
means an even bigger event, which
means more fortune for your town
or city! Supposedly.
41:
This is just the thing Palpebra needs
to spice things up for the new year,
don't you think?
44:
I can't even imagine the headache
you'd have trying to put something
like this...
52:
Ellya really pulls out all the stops
when it comes to Palpebra, huh?
57:
I'll be counting on your help at the
checkpoints today, everybody!
61: You got it. Let's mosey, people.
66:
Okay, lookin' good. We've really
gotta nail this if we want it to
become an annual tradition.
71:
Without further ado, ladies and
gentlemen! Let us commence... the
inaugural Palpebra Fortunebringer
Race!
74:
The rules are easy enough. Run your
way throughout town into the forest.
The first person to touch the giant
boulder wins!
78:
On top of the coveted
Fortunebringer title, the winner will
also receive a magical gemstone
generously provided by the guild!
84:
That oughtta get them fired up!
Okay, folks. I want a nice, clean, race.
Got it?
99:
...
I'm gettin' kinda antsy... I think I'm
gonna go check it out!
110:
This scumbag here was tripping the
other racers on purpose.
112:
I disqualified him, but he started
gettin' a bit rowdy, so I... I shut him
down, so to speak.
116:
Huh... I guess that would be the right
call in this situation.
119:
What I don't get is why someone
would do this. There's nothing of
ACTUAL value on the line here.
123:
On the other hand, there might be
someone with something to gain in
another sense...
129:
Keep an eye out for any more
troublemakers, Nimbus, I'm gonna
go check the other checkpoints!
134:
H-hey! Calm down, everyone!
What's the big idea?!
143:
Ellya! Someone started charging
into the crowd, and a whole brawl
broke out!
145:
I've barely been able to keep them
under control, but everyone's too
heated to listen to me!
150:
Ellya, listen! A few racers have found
themselves unable to go any
farthersomeone's been setting
down traps apparently!
155:
Hmm... How many people reached
your checkpoint so far?
161:
Just one, actually. I found it to be
strange that someone would be so
far ahead of everyone else, so I went
back to check.
167:
Just one, huh? Thanks. I think I see
what's happening here.
169:
Someone is trying to rig the race so
that a certain racer takes first prize!
And it's not only a single person, but
a coordinated effort!
175:
Once I find out who they are... Oooh,
they'd better HOPE I don't find them!
182:
Stop right there, cheater scum! I'm
afraid I can't let you win this race.
185:
What's the big idea? It's not my fault
the other racers are just slow! Go
kick rocks!
189:
I said I wanted to see a nice, clean
race... Didn't I?
192:
Yeah, well... where's your proof? I
won this race fair and square, and
you've got nothin'!
194: Nothin', huh? How about this then?!
204:
The Fortunebringer was supposed to
be a symbol of hope and prosperity
for Palpebra! How dare you
besmirch its name!
209:
Er... Did you just touch the
race-winning boulder?
214: Oh, oops! Uh, that one doesn't count!
218:
But there's nobody else left in this
raceliterally!
223:
And so I guess that makes you
Palpebra's Fortunebringer! What a
get for the Starlight Sharpshooter!
226: Let's hear it for our champion!
231:
Wait, that's gotta be against the
rules or something, right? And I
didn't even mean to touch the
stupid boulder!
235:
But listen to that crowd! I've never
heard them so fired up before!
238:
ELLYA won the race?! You've gotta
be kidding me!
239:
I'm gonna enter and take the title for
myself next year!
249:
Fine. I guess since there isn't anyone
else available to take the title, I'll
take it tentatively.
250:
Don't like it? Try to take it back from
me next year!
254: Heh-heh. Way to play the heel, Ellya.
257: Phew... All's well that ends well, I think.
261:
Once Ellya gets involved with
something, people get talking.
Perhaps this was the outcome she
was hoping for all along.
